Self-reported presence was the averaged response to five, five-point Likert scale questions, [(
   M = 3.16; 
   SD = 0.92), min = 1.60, max = 4.80] in the post-survey that measured the degree to which participants felt surrounded by the virtual environment.

We also tracked the participants' viewpoint through the virtual world, which let us calculate the total distance traveled underwater across three zones, [(
   M = 128.12 m; 
   SD = 37.17 m), min = 45.49 m, max = 193.26 m].
